<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 06 at 9:02AM EST  by NWS Albany</headline>
<description>..SPOTTY LIGHT FREEZING RAIN OR FREEZING DRIZZLE POSSIBLE THIS
MORNING...
Patchy, light freezing rain will occur across some spots in the
the southern Adirondacks, Mohawk Valley, and Lake George Saratoga
Region, where some sub freezing temperatures are occurring at the
surface. The threat for the spotty light freezing rain will end by
noon today. A light glaze of ice could form on untreated surfaces
Temperatures will rise from the lower 30s to above freezing
thereafter. Some slick spots may occur on untreated surfaces.
Motorists should drive with extra caution in the early to mid
morning hours.</description>
